 and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Roger Launcelyn was born in 1405, in Hampshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Roger Launcelyn. She died in 1461, in her hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1405–1461":"1405–1461","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1434–1510":"1434–1510","1434":"1434","1510":"1510","1400":"1400","1461":"1461","1405":"1405","Launcelynbury, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England"},"fi":{"1405–1461":"1405–1461","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1434–1510":"1434–1510","1434":"1434","1510":"1510","1400":"1400","1461":"1461","1405":"1405","Launcelynbury, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England"},"fr":{"1405–1461":"1405–1461","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1434–1510":"1434–1510","1434":"1434","1510":"1510","1400":"1400","1461":"1461","1405":"1405","Launcelynbury, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hampshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Roger Launcelyn est née en 1405, à Hampshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Roger Launcelyn. Elle est décédée en 1461, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 56 ans."},"de":{"1405–1461":"1405–1461","1400–1461":"1400–1461","1434–1510":"1434–1510","1434":"1434","1510"